external_knowledge:
; The 'specific notification date' refers to the date when a notification was sent, presumably to trigger or mark the beginning of a new reporting period or update cycle; 
; 'population size' is represented by the square root of the country's population; 
; 'percentage of total cases' is calculated as the total number of cases divided by the country's population, then multiplied by 100 and truncated to an integer.
